And Texas suddenly. And he was a member of the NAACP.

04:13:20.600 --> 04:13:28.600
And I knew him, I kind of knew of him, because I knew his sister worked for us in the cap agents.

04:13:28.600 --> 04:13:38.600
So when he learned about Mrs. Hamer's death, that next morning, he showed up in my office in Indian old.

04:13:39.600 --> 04:13:48.600
And I told him what the situation was. And he said, don't worry. We'll bury Mrs. Hamer on that property.

04:13:48.600 --> 04:13:57.600
So I let that alone for the right then. Now, what about our funeral? You know?

04:13:57.600 --> 04:14:02.600
So, everybody's got me stuck with this. You see what I'm talking about?

04:14:03.600 --> 04:14:14.600
So, man again, I'm frightened. And when I got to remove them, Owen Brooks was at Mrs. Hamer's house.

04:14:14.600 --> 04:14:23.600
And I told him that Henry Espy had to bury him.

04:14:23.600 --> 04:14:31.600
