04:14:36.600 --> 04:14:41.600
And so, he said, Mac, I've started to make these nights.

04:14:41.600 --> 04:14:45.600
I've been calling these people. I've been doing this. And I've been doing that.

04:14:45.600 --> 04:14:51.600
I said, you got to, you, you plan it. Or, I said, you got it.

04:14:51.600 --> 04:14:56.600
And he gladly accepted it. You know? And he talked with Henry.

04:14:57.600 --> 04:15:03.600
And then later, I learned that it's going to cost nearly $10,000. That's their only reason.

04:15:03.600 --> 04:15:11.600
The count of funeral that Henry has here, it was over $8,000, and almost $9,000 to $10,000.

04:15:11.600 --> 04:15:20.600
The three of us, Unison and Jim and have signed papers to them and given them by the, to the man.

04:15:21.600 --> 04:15:27.600
Don't worry about the call. But it's cost nearly $10,000.

04:15:27.600 --> 04:15:34.600
And so, now what happened was, after Owen got that, I was relieved.

04:15:34.600 --> 04:15:45.600
All right. And then that afternoon, Cleve came and said that he had met with the City Board of Allerman and Enruvel.

04:15:46.600 --> 04:15:52.600
And at that time, the City had, Eruvel had a female man, Dr. Virginia Talbert.

04:15:52.600 --> 04:16:00.600
And she had passed a resolution doing Mrs. Hamer Day when Mrs. Hamlet was sick,

04:16:00.600 --> 04:16:07.600
making Hamer Day, designating Hamer Day. And we had had a big gathering and everything.

04:16:07.600 --> 04:16:13.600
And she had spoke, nice lady by a Mississippi standards.

04:16:13.600 --> 04:16:29.600
So, Henry Espy and Owen got together on the burial and Cleve created the legal thing and had that set up.

04:16:29.600 --> 04:16:35.600
And so, she could be buried then. And Henry Espy had the body.

04:16:35.600 --> 04:16:43.600
Now, all I had to do now was try to take this pressure off my heart, need.

04:16:43.600 --> 04:16:50.600
And so, when I learned that it was, it was causing, what it was causing the burial,

04:16:50.600 --> 04:16:57.600
then I wouldn't told my friends, they said, man, we got, we got no $10,000.

04:16:57.600 --> 04:17:05.600
But Owen Brooks had agreed to take care of this.

04:17:05.600 --> 04:17:11.600
And at that time, Delta Ministry was, he was the director of Delta Ministry.

04:17:11.600 --> 04:17:23.600
And Charles Bannerman was the president and CEO of MACE (Mississippi Action for Community Education) + MACE (Mississippi Action for Community Education) + Delta Foundation, a MACE (Mississippi Action for Community Education) + Delta Foundation.

04:17:23.600 --> 04:17:31.600
So, MACE (Mississippi Action for Community Education) + Delta Foundation paid the, paid the bill. And we buried her.

04:17:31.600 --> 04:17:38.600
And out there, and wasn't on, nothing out there but her grave site.

04:17:38.600 --> 04:17:48.600
And in one of my papers, I wrote after that, that I hope that someday somebody here in this town

04:17:48.600 --> 04:17:57.600
would pick this up and run with. And 10 things over the years, there were a lot of, you know,

04:17:57.600 --> 04:18:08.600
there were some of the people, some people had me arrested about donating that property to, for them to be buried.

04:18:08.600 --> 04:18:17.600
And so, over the years, nothing happened with that grave site for several years.

04:18:17.600 --> 04:18:23.600
And then a little later, in ruralville, working for the Head Start program,

04:18:23.600 --> 04:18:28.600
raised some money and put a headstone out there.

04:18:28.600 --> 04:18:37.600
Head Start people raised that money. And then later, later named Pat Thompson,

04:18:37.600 --> 04:18:48.600
a graduate of Delta State at MARA of Mrs. Hamon, Victoria Gray Adams and the mother started to hold some means out there

04:18:48.600 --> 04:18:59.600
and had it Bennie G. Thompson and others. And then slowly, the things started to develop.

04:18:59.600 --> 04:19:07.600
And this had a jaw and the lady who is over the thing now now got elected to the board of all of them.

04:19:07.600 --> 04:19:16.600
And she worked with the city to get a self-help grant to put the provision out there.

04:19:16.600 --> 04:19:24.600
And some other people, white and black, help come up with some of the monuments and things out there.

04:19:24.600 --> 04:19:33.600
And I made a promise that one day I would have her standing in the Delta.

04:19:33.600 --> 04:19:45.600
You know, I saw a picture of her standing in a cotton field looking back she was surveying over the area.

04:19:45.600 --> 04:19:52.600
And so I was able to sail that idea to several people and to Pat Thompson.

04:19:52.600 --> 04:20:06.600
And up in New Jersey, people up there had been carrying on a program in Mrs. Hamer's honor since she spoke up there back in the credentials committee.

04:20:06.600 --> 04:20:18.600
